WEBVTT

00:03.133 --> 00:03.567
Previously on "Below Deck"...

00:05.266 --> 00:06.700
[thud!]
God damn it!

00:06.700 --> 00:08.500
I can promise you
there's gonna be a change

00:08.500 --> 00:10.367
in the configuration
of this crew.

00:10.367 --> 00:13.567
- I hope that Lee just cans
one of these f---ers.

00:13.567 --> 00:15.133
- Are you a new crew
or something?

00:15.133 --> 00:16.367
- The new boatswain.

00:16.367 --> 00:18.300
EJ.
- Nice to meet you.

00:21.567 --> 00:22.700
- You're sleeping
in the crew mess.

00:22.700 --> 00:24.633
- Well, of course.

00:24.633 --> 00:26.467
They're just trying to f---
with me at this point.

00:28.700 --> 00:30.266
You brought me
to a nude beach?

00:30.266 --> 00:31.767
Oh, my gosh.
- You're an asshole.

00:31.767 --> 00:33.367
You're a horrible date.
Let's get f---ed up.

00:33.367 --> 00:35.133
Partying and drinking

00:35.133 --> 00:36.667
kind of ruined
my relationship with my ex.

00:36.667 --> 00:38.700
Now I've probably just
embarrassed myself.

00:38.700 --> 00:40.433
- I've been working my ass off,

00:40.433 --> 00:42.467
but Bri's getting
the entire afternoon off.

00:42.467 --> 00:45.033
It's not fair.
- Bradley and Summer Smith.

00:45.033 --> 00:46.333
Also a trained gourmet chef.

00:46.333 --> 00:47.700
- How's everything so far?

00:47.700 --> 00:49.433
- My steak
is way past medium.

00:49.433 --> 00:51.600
- That's a problem.
Risotto was underdone.

00:51.600 --> 00:53.033
- Oh, no.

00:53.033 --> 00:54.600
This brake wasn't disengaged.

00:54.600 --> 00:56.433
That's all the metal.
- Oh, sh--.

00:56.433 --> 00:58.600
- What a f---ing idiot.

00:58.600 --> 01:00.000
[horn blares]

01:00.000 --> 01:03.066
[upbeat music]

01:03.066 --> 01:10.066
♪ ♪

01:15.166 --> 01:19.033
[light upbeat music]

01:19.033 --> 01:20.500
- Can I get anybody

01:20.500 --> 01:23.233
something to drink
besides sparkling water?

01:23.233 --> 01:25.100
- Sparkling water sounds great.

01:25.100 --> 01:26.734
- Yay.

01:26.734 --> 01:30.066
- Charter four,
the most boring charter ever.

01:30.066 --> 01:32.333
- All right,
let's get out of here.

01:32.333 --> 01:34.200
- Lot of friction,

01:34.200 --> 01:35.734
which isn't good for it.

01:35.734 --> 01:37.367
- It's strange that it would
even move, right?

01:37.367 --> 01:40.367
- It's really straineous on it,
but it'll do it.

01:40.367 --> 01:43.300
- I should have checked it.
But I thought

01:43.300 --> 01:44.567
that he would have
already done that.

01:44.567 --> 01:46.333
- Well, that's why it's so hot.

01:46.333 --> 01:48.300
The gears are working
up against the brake,

01:48.300 --> 01:49.767
which isn't good for it.

01:49.767 --> 01:52.033
- I got to double-check
everything,

01:52.033 --> 01:54.700
'cause these guys are just
a bunch of numbdies.

01:59.033 --> 02:00.633
- Jen, if you'll go
flip laundry real quick

02:00.633 --> 02:01.667
and then come right back up.

02:01.667 --> 02:04.567
- Okay.

02:08.266 --> 02:10.734
[sighs]

02:10.734 --> 02:12.734
I've been working harder
than Bri.

02:12.734 --> 02:16.500
I don't think that Kate's
trying to wear me down

02:16.500 --> 02:18.667
to the point of me quitting,

02:18.667 --> 02:22.066
but I do know that it sucks
to be me right now.

02:22.066 --> 02:23.734
I'm killing it.

02:25.266 --> 02:27.133
- When we pull that anchor,

02:27.133 --> 02:29.266
I don't care if it's him
setting it up.

02:29.266 --> 02:31.133
I want you to check it.
- Okay.

02:31.133 --> 02:34.200
- 'Cause he just pulled it up
with the hand brake on.

02:37.133 --> 02:38.400
- Well, try to.

02:38.400 --> 02:40.266
- Like, picture a brake
on a bicycle.

02:40.266 --> 02:42.066
You're running down a hill,
and you're holding it down,

02:42.066 --> 02:43.266
and you're pedaling
at the same time.

02:50.033 --> 02:52.166
- There's a reason
why I'm here.

02:52.166 --> 02:54.767
Captain Lee called me because
things aren't being run right.

02:56.233 --> 02:57.533
- Pull it. Pull it.
Pull it. Pull it.

02:57.533 --> 02:58.567
- Whoa.
[thud!]

02:58.567 --> 02:59.767
- What the f--- now?

02:59.767 --> 03:01.233
- The overall feeling on board

03:01.233 --> 03:03.000
is not where it should be.

03:03.000 --> 03:04.633
He knows his stuff,
and I know my stuff.

03:04.633 --> 03:06.700
- I want you to check it
even if it's him pulling it.

03:10.500 --> 03:12.133
- Yeah.

03:12.133 --> 03:13.367
- At least I know
you've done it every time.

03:16.233 --> 03:18.166
- All right, Matt,
what's on the schedule today?

03:18.166 --> 03:19.700
- Lunch on board with, like,
the lobster and--

03:19.700 --> 03:21.300
- That sounds perfect.
- Okay.

03:21.300 --> 03:23.100
- I appreciate that.
- No worries.

03:23.100 --> 03:25.133
Last night, I think I may have
blown the dinner.

03:25.133 --> 03:27.000
- So the risotto's
a little underdone.

03:27.000 --> 03:29.033
- All right.
- I need to put

03:29.033 --> 03:31.033
my personal sh-- aside
and focus on the meal.

03:31.033 --> 03:32.066
That's the plan.
Thank you.

03:32.066 --> 03:33.066
- Thank you.

03:33.066 --> 03:34.667
- [sighs]

03:34.667 --> 03:37.033
[upbeat music]

03:37.033 --> 03:39.066
- Oh, sh--.

03:39.066 --> 03:41.266
We got a little leakage
in the laundry room, girls.

03:41.266 --> 03:42.467
- Wait, are they both
overflowing?

03:42.467 --> 03:44.266
- They both.
- Ugh!

03:46.433 --> 03:47.433
[both laugh]

03:47.433 --> 03:49.166
Jen.
[laughs]

03:49.166 --> 03:52.200
- [sighs]
- I have more patience with Jen

03:52.200 --> 03:54.467
because I know, like,
yachting is very new to her.

03:54.467 --> 03:59.367
But I find myself feeling like
I'm almost doing more work.

04:04.734 --> 04:07.633
Yeah, I know.

04:07.633 --> 04:11.066
- Jen, Jen, Kate.

04:11.066 --> 04:12.633
- Go ahead.

04:12.633 --> 04:15.100
- Yeah, can you come
to the stew pantry, please?

04:15.100 --> 04:17.600
How much soap did you put
in the washers?

04:17.600 --> 04:19.367
- Not much.
Why?

04:19.367 --> 04:21.233
- Because apparently
both of them were foaming

04:21.233 --> 04:22.734
out the top and the bottom.

04:22.734 --> 04:25.066
So let's see which soap
you used.

04:25.066 --> 04:26.367
- I have been busting my butt.

04:26.367 --> 04:28.367
- Just to...

04:28.367 --> 04:30.600
- You could probably use
a quarter of that.

04:30.600 --> 04:32.233
- But with Kate,

04:32.233 --> 04:33.500
I don't think I can ever
do anything right.

04:33.500 --> 04:35.767
- Let's just use less soap.

04:35.767 --> 04:37.700
- Oh, man!

04:37.700 --> 04:39.633
- Okay, this is one of
the most beautiful places

04:39.633 --> 04:40.700
I've ever been.

04:40.700 --> 04:45.367
♪ ♪

04:45.367 --> 04:47.100
- Is that "Eclipse"?

04:47.100 --> 04:49.400
- Yeah, and there's
the "Maltese Falcon."

04:49.400 --> 04:51.400
- Crazy, dude.
All the big girls here today.

04:51.400 --> 04:53.467
- We in Ballerville?
- Yeah, mon.

04:53.467 --> 04:55.266
- We're in high season
in St. Barts.

04:55.266 --> 04:56.667
- There's some big boys
over there.

04:56.667 --> 04:59.133
- Leonardo DiCaprio,
Mark Wahlberg.

04:59.133 --> 05:00.667
Everybody who's anybody

05:00.667 --> 05:03.266
is typically in St. Barts
right now.

05:03.266 --> 05:05.266
- You guys ready on the stern?
- Yes, sir.

05:05.266 --> 05:08.133
Standing by.
- Drop now.

05:08.133 --> 05:10.133
- Two shots out.

05:10.133 --> 05:12.667
- Okay, let's get some toys
in the water for these guys.

05:12.667 --> 05:13.767
- You ready?
Gonna get in the water?

05:13.767 --> 05:15.133
- I love it.

05:15.133 --> 05:17.066
- Let's get the slide over.

05:17.066 --> 05:18.767
[grunts]
It's down.

05:20.133 --> 05:21.667
- Ooh-ya-ka!

05:21.667 --> 05:24.600
- All right, cheesy tourist
down the slide.

05:24.600 --> 05:26.333
- There you go, right?
[laughs]

05:26.333 --> 05:27.333
[upbeat music]

05:27.333 --> 05:30.033
♪ ♪

05:30.033 --> 05:32.367
- Whoa.
- That was actually hilarious.

05:32.367 --> 05:34.567
- All right, Fred, you got
style points for that.

05:34.567 --> 05:37.633
♪ ♪

05:37.633 --> 05:40.133
- Hey.
- Can I ask your advice?

05:40.133 --> 05:42.500
- Yeah.
- You've been in yachting

05:42.500 --> 05:44.266
a lot longer than I have,
obviously.

05:44.266 --> 05:46.533
- Yeah.
- Um, I'm in a weird spot,

05:46.533 --> 05:48.033
like, sleeping
in the crew mess, you know?

05:48.033 --> 05:50.033
- Yeah.

05:50.033 --> 05:51.700
- How long do you think
we'll have EJ with us for?

05:51.700 --> 05:53.500
- He's gonna be with us
as long as we need him

05:53.500 --> 05:56.166
to be with us.
I really feel bad for Chris.

05:56.166 --> 05:58.233
I think he's actually handling
his situation

05:58.233 --> 06:00.000
pretty well,
all things considered.

06:00.000 --> 06:01.700
- I'm thinking about sleeping
in the bilge.

06:01.700 --> 06:03.533
- If I were you, I would
just take the bilge,

06:03.533 --> 06:05.767
be happy for the extra help
on deck,

06:05.767 --> 06:07.767
learn everything you can,

06:07.767 --> 06:09.533
and go make that bilge
your own.

06:09.533 --> 06:10.567
- That's good advice.

06:10.567 --> 06:12.100
[laughter]

06:17.600 --> 06:18.600
- Sure.

06:20.467 --> 06:23.066
- Oh, sh--.

06:23.066 --> 06:25.266
It's so bizarre.
I know I had lobster.

06:25.266 --> 06:26.734
I don't have lobster
on the boat.

06:26.734 --> 06:29.000
I've promised the guest
fresh lobster.

06:29.000 --> 06:30.467
That's not good.

06:30.467 --> 06:31.533
Captain, Captain, Matt.
- Go, Matt.

06:35.467 --> 06:38.300
- Copy that. I could have
Nick go on the "Intrepid."

06:38.300 --> 06:40.433
- So they're going to get
the lobsters fresh for lunch?

06:40.433 --> 06:42.066
- Yeah.

06:42.066 --> 06:43.333
- Matt doesn't think ahead
too much.

06:43.333 --> 06:45.333
- Awesome.

06:45.333 --> 06:46.600
- Should we dry the decks?

06:46.600 --> 06:48.000
- Um...
- Or the bow first?

06:48.000 --> 06:49.433
- He's doing that right now,

06:49.433 --> 06:51.200
so me and you,
why don't we concentrate?

06:51.200 --> 06:53.100
We'll get that knocked out
and then help them.

06:53.100 --> 06:54.400
- Roger.

06:57.567 --> 06:59.066
- Hey, Baker?

06:59.066 --> 07:00.734
Let's hold this off till later,

07:00.734 --> 07:02.200
'cause this isn't a guest area.

07:02.200 --> 07:04.166
So let's just finish
the main deck.

07:04.166 --> 07:06.033
- Okay, roger.

07:06.033 --> 07:09.233
EJ was wanting to dry here,
so I'll just...

07:09.233 --> 07:11.166
- What's that?

07:11.166 --> 07:12.633
- Me and EJ were just like,
"Well"--

07:12.633 --> 07:14.300
I asked him which side
we should dry first,

07:14.300 --> 07:15.633
and he was like,
"Let's do the bow," but...

07:15.633 --> 07:17.200
- Yeah, we'll do
guest areas instead.

07:17.200 --> 07:18.734
- Word.

07:18.734 --> 07:20.233
- I don't think the guests
are gonna be hanging out

07:20.233 --> 07:21.633
with the anchors too much.

07:21.633 --> 07:23.233
- I don't want
to piss anyone off

07:23.233 --> 07:25.367
or hurt anyone's feelings.

07:25.367 --> 07:27.300
At the end of the day,
they're both my boss,

07:27.300 --> 07:31.000
so I just want to just do
whatever I'm told, I guess.

07:35.333 --> 07:37.333
- Deck crew,
deck crew, Matt.

07:37.333 --> 07:40.000
Do you know if Nick is back
with the lobsters yet?

07:40.000 --> 07:42.133
- Uh, no, he's not back yet,
Matt.

07:42.133 --> 07:43.667
- F---.

07:43.667 --> 07:44.667
Okay.

07:44.667 --> 07:46.266
Come on.

07:46.266 --> 07:47.600
- Everybody's hungry.

07:48.600 --> 07:50.533
- 12:45.
- I'm starving.

07:50.533 --> 07:52.233
- Has your lobster come yet?

07:52.233 --> 07:53.734
- No, it hasn't come yet.

07:55.600 --> 07:58.100
- The lobster would be
fantastic.

07:59.600 --> 08:02.600
- We are drifting
into the "Maltese Falcon."

08:02.600 --> 08:04.200
- We're gonna f---ing hit 'em.

08:04.200 --> 08:05.266
- Go the other way then.
- Son of a bitch.

08:05.266 --> 08:06.333
- Brace yourself.

08:10.000 --> 08:10.433
- Deck crew, deck crew, Matt.

08:12.734 --> 08:14.600
Do you know if Nick is back
with the lobsters yet?

08:14.600 --> 08:16.066
- No, he's not back yet, Matt.

08:16.066 --> 08:17.567
- F---.

08:17.567 --> 08:19.300
- Sparkling for you?
- What time is it?

08:19.300 --> 08:21.367
- 12:50.
- I'm starving.

08:21.367 --> 08:26.033
- Where is that guy?
- Lobster would be fantastic.

08:27.266 --> 08:28.700
- My guests are dying
out there.

08:28.700 --> 08:31.133
- [yawns]
- Your lobster come yet?

08:31.133 --> 08:33.133
- No, it hasn't come yet.
It's on its way.

08:33.133 --> 08:34.767
- Are the salads ready? 'Cause
we could get 'em started.

08:34.767 --> 08:36.433
- Yeah, sure.
- What's the dressing?

08:36.433 --> 08:39.300
- There's a lemon vinegar
dressing on there.

08:39.300 --> 08:41.433
- Lemon vinegar.

08:41.433 --> 08:44.033
- Oh, f---.
I'm freaking out right now.

08:44.033 --> 08:45.700
I promised these guests
lobsters,

08:45.700 --> 08:47.166
and now the lobsters
aren't on the boat.

08:47.166 --> 08:48.633
And this is a problem.

08:48.633 --> 08:51.166
- So to start, we have
a Romaine salad

08:51.166 --> 08:52.700
with sun-dried tomatoes
and cheddar

08:52.700 --> 08:55.667
with a lemon vinegar dressing.

08:55.667 --> 08:57.567
Pardon.

09:00.400 --> 09:01.734
- Oh, it's great.

09:01.734 --> 09:03.266
- I love those
heirloom tomatoes.

09:03.266 --> 09:04.600
They're so good.
- Mm-hmm.

09:04.600 --> 09:06.200
- And then behind you,
we've got

09:06.200 --> 09:09.066
some very, very fresh
lobster tail.

09:14.333 --> 09:15.600
We are all over
the place.

09:15.600 --> 09:17.300
Ugh!
It's so frustrating.

09:17.300 --> 09:18.600
- Just because someone's been

09:18.600 --> 09:20.200
in the yachting industry
for a while

09:20.200 --> 09:21.467
doesn't mean they know
what they're doing.

09:22.467 --> 09:23.467
- Hey, guys.

09:25.133 --> 09:26.667
- Live lobsters coming in.

09:26.667 --> 09:29.133
- Nick, can you run that
to the galley, please?

09:29.133 --> 09:30.166
- Galley?

09:34.033 --> 09:36.467
- Watch out.
Lobster coming through.

09:36.467 --> 09:37.667
- Are the tails gonna be
in the shell

09:37.667 --> 09:39.333
or out of the shell?

09:39.333 --> 09:41.233
- I'm gonna cook them
in the shell.

09:41.233 --> 09:42.333
I'm gonna take them out
and then put them back in.

09:42.333 --> 09:43.700
- Okay, shell bowls.

09:43.700 --> 09:45.300
- Ugh!

09:46.467 --> 09:48.633
- Oh!
They're full-bodied.

09:48.633 --> 09:49.767
Are they alive right now?

09:49.767 --> 09:51.033
- No, they're not alive now.

09:52.633 --> 09:54.200
- Ugh!

09:54.200 --> 09:55.633
- Oh, I don't like
that they're moving!

09:55.633 --> 09:58.033
- Oh, it's a family!

10:00.367 --> 10:02.300
How long on the lobster?

10:02.300 --> 10:05.000
- Right now.
- Okay.

10:06.233 --> 10:09.567
Yum, yum.
- Oh, it's beautiful.

10:09.567 --> 10:11.633
We had a lobster miracle.

10:11.633 --> 10:14.467
Well, not for the lobsters.

10:14.467 --> 10:16.333
- They just came down.

10:16.333 --> 10:17.367
Fresh local lobster.

10:17.367 --> 10:18.633
- Wow.
- Awesome.

10:18.633 --> 10:20.233
- Amazing!
- Thank you.

10:20.233 --> 10:23.533
- Pardon me.
Thank you.

10:23.533 --> 10:24.667
- That doesn't get any better.

10:24.667 --> 10:26.266
Matt is on fire.

10:26.266 --> 10:27.467
- Oh, good.
I'm so glad.

10:27.467 --> 10:28.633
- These are awesome.

10:28.633 --> 10:29.667
- Matt?
- Yup.

10:29.667 --> 10:31.200
- They love the lobsters.

10:31.200 --> 10:32.266
- Thanks, Kate.
- Mm-hmm.

10:32.266 --> 10:33.667
- Appreciate it.

10:33.667 --> 10:35.400
- All right, Chris.
- Say what?

10:35.400 --> 10:38.000
- You and I have to zip
these two cushions up.

10:38.000 --> 10:39.033
- Let's do it.

10:42.367 --> 10:44.400
- Water toys in the water.

10:44.400 --> 10:46.266
Can we throw a Jet Ski
in the water?

10:46.266 --> 10:48.100
- Absolutely, yeah.
I'll drop it down right away.

10:50.400 --> 10:53.734
- Moving a little screwy
off the release.

10:53.734 --> 10:57.000
- Okay, sir.
We can attach it here.

10:57.000 --> 10:58.734
You take a Jet Ski
as well?

10:58.734 --> 11:00.266
Absolutely.

11:00.266 --> 11:01.700
- We're making moves here.

11:05.367 --> 11:08.133
- A little sunset spin, huh?

11:11.166 --> 11:13.433
- So, Matt...
- Yes.

11:13.433 --> 11:15.166
- These people are not
drinking.

11:15.166 --> 11:16.533
- Right.
- They're not really

11:16.533 --> 11:18.166
into anything but food.

11:18.166 --> 11:21.567
So he wants "a tasting
of Caribbean."

11:21.567 --> 11:25.166
- I don't see anything
real goofy about the cuisines.

11:25.166 --> 11:27.500
He wants some tasting menus.

11:27.500 --> 11:31.166
- I just want
to communicate that to you now.

11:31.166 --> 11:33.700
I would just--
whatever you're gonna make

11:33.700 --> 11:35.700
and then kick it up
a little extra.

11:35.700 --> 11:37.633
- Gotcha.
Kate's right.

11:37.633 --> 11:40.400
I need to put my sh-- aside
and focus on the meal tonight.

11:40.400 --> 11:42.266
- We already have
an extra deckhand,

11:42.266 --> 11:44.567
which could possibly mean
less tip for all of us.

11:44.567 --> 11:47.533
Tonight is the night
to really bring the A game.

11:49.567 --> 11:51.300
- Tearing it up out there?

11:51.300 --> 11:53.567
- That was awesome.
I would do that again.

11:56.734 --> 11:59.734
[pulsing music]

11:59.734 --> 12:03.200
♪ ♪

12:03.200 --> 12:05.600
- Never, never, ever
without a shirt.

12:05.600 --> 12:07.367
You never know when a guest
is gonna come up.

12:09.166 --> 12:10.567
- That's what those shirts
are made for:

12:10.567 --> 12:11.734
to be wet.

12:15.000 --> 12:16.734
- You know what?

12:16.734 --> 12:19.667
Some of these windows
are still a little salty.

12:19.667 --> 12:22.467
There's just still some salt
on the windows,

12:22.467 --> 12:24.533
so I'm getting ready
to go around to do that.

12:24.533 --> 12:26.533
It's super caked on it.

12:26.533 --> 12:28.233
- Bruno's been doing
the windows; it's been fine.

12:28.233 --> 12:30.066
So he'll do his way.
You do your way.

12:30.066 --> 12:31.333
And life is good.

12:31.333 --> 12:33.066
- Yeah, but in the end
of the day,

12:33.066 --> 12:34.467
this is how it turns out,
so it's like--

12:34.467 --> 12:35.500
- Who did these windows?

12:35.500 --> 12:37.100
- He rinsed these windows,

12:37.100 --> 12:38.500
